exec
/bin/bash -lc "nl -ba content/papers/ghost.modes.md | sed -n '1,240p'" in /home/dave/Projects/jaynes-archive succeeded in 51ms:
     1	---
     2	title: "Ghost Modes in Imperfect Waveguides"
     3	author: ["E.T. Jaynes"]
     4	year: 1958
     5	abstract: >
     6	  Attention is called to the existence of microwave resonances
     7	  which have the unusual property that they are nonradiating, and thus
     8	  have high Q, in spite of the fact that the fields are not enclosed
     9	  completely by metallic walls. These "ghost modes" represent fields
    10	  which are derived from those of the usual waveguide modes, but are
    11	  "trapped" in the vicinity of imperfections in the waveguide. Their
    12	  resonant frequency is slightly lower than the corresponding cutoff
    13	  frequency. If one attempts to use a waveguide in its lowest mode, over
    14	  a range of frequencies which includes the ghosts of higher modes,
    15	  complicated resonance effects may be observed which can cause trouble
    16	  in some types of microwave circuits. The same phenomenon exists in any
    17	  structure which has pass bands and rejection bands, such as periodic
    18	  structures or crystals.
    19	---
    20	# Introduction
